---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const today = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];
---
<Base title="Privacy Policy — e-ComGen Design" description="Privacy policy for e-comgen.site and e-ComGen Design products.">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 prose prose-navy text-navy/80 leading-relaxed">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-navy/50">Last updated: {today}</p>

    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      e-ComGen Design ("we", "us") operates the website <a href="https://e-comgen.site">e-comgen.site</a>
      and sells digital design assets (SVG icon packs) through Gumroad
      (<a href="https://ecomgendesign.gumroad.com">ecomgendesign.gumroad.com</a>).
      Contact: <code>hello@e-comgen.site</code>
    </p>

    <h2>What data we collect</h2>
    <p>This website is a static site (HTML, CSS, images). We do <strong>not</strong> collect personal data directly:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>No login or account system</li>
      <li>No tracking cookies set by us</li>
      <li>No analytics scripts that identify individuals</li>
      <li>No newsletter form on this site (subscribe happens on Gumroad)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What our hosting provider sees</h2>
    <p>
      The site is hosted on Cloudflare. Cloudflare logs basic request data (IP address, user agent, referrer)
      for security and performance reasons. See
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cloudflare's privacy policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party services we link to</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Gumroad</strong> — handles all purchases. When you click "Buy" or "Get free" you go to gumroad.com. They collect your email and (for paid orders) payment details under their own
        <a href="https://gumroad.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">privacy policy</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>GitHub</strong> — hosts our free icon previews. Visiting our GitHub repos is governed by
        <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub's privacy statement</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Pinterest</strong> — we use Pinterest's API to publish pins for our products. We do not collect Pinterest user data.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      This site does not set its own cookies. Cloudflare may set a security cookie (<code>__cf_bm</code>) to
      detect bots. This expires after 30 minutes and contains no personal data.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Since we don't collect personal data on this website, there's no personal data to access, correct, or delete.
      For purchases made through Gumroad, see Gumroad's privacy controls. To contact us about anything,
      email <code>hello@e-comgen.site</code>.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We'll update the date at the top of this page when this policy changes. Material changes will be
      announced on the homepage.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
